Есть несколько способов записи текущего времени в файл с использованием библиотеки `<chrono>`:

1. Использование `std::chrono::system_clock::now()`:

```cpp
auto now = std::chrono::system_clock::now();
std::time_t time = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(now);
std::string strTime = std::ctime(&time);

std::ofstream outputFile("log.txt", std::ios::app);
outputFile << strTime << ": " << event << std::endl;
outputFile.close();
```

2. Использование `std::chrono::time_point` и `std::chrono::duration`:

```cpp
auto now = std::chrono::system_clock::now();
std::time_t time = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(now);
std::tm* tm = std::localtime(&time);

std::ostringstream oss;
oss << std::put_time(tm, "%c");

std::ofstream outputFile("log.txt", std::ios::app);
outputFile << oss.str() << ": " << event << std::endl;
outputFile.close();
```

3. Использование `std::strftime`:
```cpp
auto now = std::chrono::system_clock::now();
std::time_t time = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(now);

std::array<char, 100> buffer;
std::strftime(buffer.data(), buffer.size(), "%c", std::localtime(&time));

std::ofstream outputFile("log.txt", std::ios::app);
outputFile << buffer.data() << ": " << event << std::endl;
outputFile.close();
```

